title: DRT Series #1
description: This is an off road TT, on one of the fastest, well kept trails in Northern IN. Riders will kick-off the start of the 2009 DRT series with 1 Lap around the Winona Lake trail system. Bring the family to enjoy the venue, and all that historic Winona Lake has to offer!
course:
Length: Approx. 10 miles
Trail Type: Single track
Skill Level: Beginner to Advanced (depending on chosen trail)
Trail Description:
There are a variety of trails through diverse terrain, some smooth
and flat with wide turns, and some with steep downhills and tight
turns. The trails are full of logs, rocks, stumps and roots.
registration: Online registration is on TrueSport.com, or by mail
notes:
** Annual License or USAC MTN 1-day license must be presented or purchased to register. Licenses: One day USAC licenses will be available at registration. Everyone must sign a waiver. Fort Wayne Parks and Recreation and DRT promotions take no responsibility for the loss of property, or damage to ones self or equipment. All USAC rules apply, and insurance will be in affect. We reserve the right to change the length or the course as needed. The minimum field size is five racers, and fields may be combined to create an adequate field. Classes and Start Times XC: Men Men CAT 1: 5 laps 1:30 P.M. Men  CAT 2: 3 laps 1:32 P.M. Men CAT 3: 2 laps 1:34 P.M. Women CAT 1: 4 laps 1:36 P.M. Women CAT 2: 2 laps 1:38 P.M. Women CAT 3: 1 lap 1:40 P.M. Classes and Start Times TT: Men CAT 1: 1 lap 1:30 P.M. Men CAT 2: 1 lap 1:30 P.M. Men CAT 3: 1 lap 1:30 P.M. Women CAT 1: 1 lap 1:30 P.M. Women CAT 2: 1 lap 1:30 P.M. Women CAT 3: 1 lap 1:30 P.M.
See http://drtconsulting.net for CAT 1 payout schedule.
directions: Winona Lake is about an hour west of Fort Wayne . Take US 30 to the East side of Warsaw . Turn South / West on Center St. (Bob Evans at this intersection). Proceed for 2 more lights on Center and turn left on to Argonne Rd. Go to the stoplight, under the viaduct and straight through the intersection. The road becomes Park Ave. Follow Park Ave through the village of Winona Lakes. Continue past the city park on the right, cross over a bridge, to the next road on the left (Boys City Dr .) Follow Boys City Drive to the main entrance of the (former) Boys Club.

title: Koehlinger / Kelley IN State TT Championship
Warsaw Downtown Classic
course: .45 mile flat, fast, and exciting four-corner rectangle around the Downtown Warsaw Square.
registration: Online registration at Truesport.com. On-site registration Saturday closes 15 minutes before each race. $10 for day of race signup. Riders under 18 are required to have a parent or guardian signature on strandard release form.
notes: All USAC rules apply. Event held Rain or Shine. Helmets must be worn at all times while on your bike. Free lap rule in effect. Must be present to receive prizes/awards. Purse may be adjusted per class if the field does not reach 40 riders per class.
directions: Located on the Courthouse Square, Downtown Warsaw, Indiana. Off US. 30, 2 miles south on St.RD. 15, west on Center St. 3 blocks
